# Template Hierarchy

## Follow WordPress Template Order
- Use specific templates before general: `single-{post-type}.php` → `single.php` → `index.php`
- Break templates into reusable parts with `get_template_part('template-parts/content', 'post')`
- Use conditional tags: `is_home()`, `is_single()`, `is_page()`, etc.

## Required Template Functions
- Include `wp_head()` before `</head>`
- Include `wp_footer()` before `</body>`
- Include `wp_body_open()` after `<body>`
- Use `body_class()` in body tag: `<body <?php body_class(); ?>>`
- Use `post_class()` in article/post wrappers

## Template Tags
- Use proper template tags: `the_title()`, `the_content()`, `the_permalink()`
- Always call `wp_reset_postdata()` after custom `WP_Query` loops
- Use `get_template_directory_uri()` for theme URLs (never hardcode)
- Use `home_url()` for site URLs (never hardcode domain)
